 local magnetic fields and the field direction can become\nreoriented. Strong magnetic fields suppress cross-field contraction and cold\nfilaments can form along or perpendicular to the initial fields.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Dec 2020 19:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 21 Aug 2021 19:41:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-24"}
