ns. We also discuss the upper limits we can place\non EM radiation from S200224ca, and the implications these limits have on the\nphysics of BBH mergers. Namely, we place a shallow upper limit on the\ndimensionless BH charge, $\\hat{q} < 1.4 \\times10^{-4}$, and an upper limit on\nthe isotropic-equivalent energy of a blast wave $E < 4.1\\times10^{51}$ erg\n(assuming typical GRB parameters).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Dec 2020 00:43:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 11 Dec 2020 19:31:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-10"}
