hat the\nwaves could be driven by p-mode flows at spatial scales smaller than the\nplumelet separation. Multiple independent sources of outflow within a single\ncoronal plume should impart significant fine structure to the solar wind that\nmay be detectable by Parker Solar Probe and Solar Orbiter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Dec 2020 15:01:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-27"}
