ntains infinitely many\ninfrared soft modes with zero energy density. These infrared modes span a\nHilbert space carrying a representation of 1-dimensional spatial\ndiffeomorphisms (or the Witt/Virasoro algebra) which are conserved charges of\nthe effective dynamics by ${\\bf H}_\\Delta$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Dec 2020 15:06:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-25"}
